      "writtenOn": "2020-02-12T01:15:45Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is intended to handle context cancellation.\n\nI added this code because Chan observed that the test (since replaced by integrationtests) I had added about checking that the routine exits after context cancellation (but not before) was flaking, i.e. sometimes failing with due to context cancellation. I noticed that the code sometimes made it after checking the current shard, and sometimes it wouldn\u0027t.\n\nDocumentation says in[1] that it\u0027s expected that the routine will _exit_ shortly after the context is canceled, and panic doesn\u0027t seem a reasonable way to handle a routine context cancellation.\n\n[1]: https://osscs.corp.google.com/chromium/infra/infra/+/master:go/src/go.chromium.org/luci/server/server.go;l\u003d702",
      "parentUuid": "6e9a2405_2e4dc6f5",
      "revId": "ad4c1fd19a76d051ecfcba100bca976d64d912a6",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
